esday/sheffield-wednesday-claude-dielna-puts-close-friendship-with-wolves-bakary-sako-on-hold-1-7158495|publisher=The Star|date=17 March 2015|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{soccerway}}\n* {{Soccerbase}}\n* {{LFP|id=dielna-claude}}\n\n{{CS Universitatea Craiova squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dielna, Claude}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:AC Ajaccio players]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:CS Sedan Ardennes players]]\n[[Category:Designated Players (MLS)]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Romania]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:French expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in Greece]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in Romania]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in Slovakia]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:French people of Guadeloupean descent]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 2 players]]\n[[Category:FC Istres players]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer players]]\n[[Category:New England Revolution players]]\n[[Category:Olympiacos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Portland Timbers players]]\n[[Category:Portland Timbers 2 players]]\n[[Category:Sheffield Wednesday F.C. players]]\n[[Category:\u0160K Slovan Bratislava players]]\n[[Category:Slovak Super Liga players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Clichy, Hauts-de-Seine]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:USL Championship players]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:FC Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:CS Universitatea Craiova players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French professional footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Claude Dielna\n| image = CINvPOR 2019-03-17 - Claude Dielna (40535773323) (cropped).jpg\n| caption = Dielna with Portland Timbers in 2019\n| fullname = Claude Pierre Marie Dielna<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.football-league.co.uk/documents/pages-from-fl-professional-retain-list-free-transfers-2014-15-2.pdf-...549-2491536.pdf |title=The Football League Limited List of Registered Players as at 16th May 2015 |publisher=The Football League |date=12 June 2015 |accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1987|12|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Clichy, Hauts-de-Seine|Clichy-la-Garenne]], France\n| height = {{height|m=1.84}}\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n| clubnumber = 4\n| youthyears1 = {{0|000}}\u20132006\n| youthclubs1 = [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132008\n| clubs1 = [[FC Lorient|Lorient]]\n| caps1 = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2008\u20132012\n| clubs2 = [[FC Istres|Istres]]\n| caps2 = 95\n| goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2012\u20132014\n| clubs3 = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos Piraeus]]\n| caps3 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[CS Sedan Ardennes|Sedan Ardennes]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 25\n| goals4 = 2\n| years5 = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs5 = \u2192 [[AC Ajaccio|Ajaccio]] (loan)\n| caps5 = 22\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2014\u20132017\n| clubs6 = [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]]\n| caps6 = 23\n| goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2015\u20132016\n| clubs7 = \u2192 [[\u0160K Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]] (loan)\n| caps7 = 4\n| goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2017\n| clubs8 = \u2192 [[FC Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti|Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti]] (loan)\n| caps8 = 10\n| goals8 = 0\n| years9 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs9 = [[New England Revolution]]\n| caps9 = 28\n| goals9 = 0\n| years10 = 2019\n| clubs10 = [[Portland Timbers]]\n| caps10 = 15\n| goals10 = 0\n| clubs11 = [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n| caps11 = 0\n| goals11 = 0\n| years11 = 2020\u2013\n| club-update = 15 October 2019\n}}\n\n'''Claude Pierre Marie Dielna''' (born 14 December 1987) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a central [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Liga I]] club [[CS Universitatea Craiova]]\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Clichy, Hauts-de-Seine|Clichy-la-Garenne]], Dielna started his career at [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]] before moving to [[FC Lorient|Lorient]], where he signed his first professional contract in April 2007, which he described as his greatest sporting joy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Les go\u00fbts et les couleurs... Claude Dielna|url=http://www.lorient.maville.com/actu/actudet_-Les-gouts-et-les-couleurs...-Claude-Dielna-P-_-618389_actu.Htm|publisher=Lorient Maville|language=French|date=19 April 2008|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=LORIENT : CONTRAT PRO POUR DIELNA|url=http://www.football365.fr/lorient-contrat-pro-pour-dielna-1203017.html|publisher=Football 365|language=French|date=20 July 2011|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> However, at Lorient, Dielna struggled to make a breakthrough at Lorient and left the club for [[FC Istres|Istres]], signing a one-year contract in the summer of 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=LORIENT : DIELNA \u00c0 ISTRES|url=http://www.football365.fr/lorient-dielna-a-istres-1203109.html|publisher=Football 365|language=French|date=20 July 2011|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nDielna was a first team regular during his time at Istres, making a total of 95 appearances for the [[Ligue 2]] team.<ref name=\"goal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sentragoal.gr/article.asp?catid=10532&subid=2&pubid=129050666|title=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03b5\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9\u03bc\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf \u039d\u03c4\u03b9\u03b5\u03bb\u03bd\u03ac (Dielna to be judged during pre-season)|last=Noikokyris|first=Giorgos|date=26 May 2012|publisher=Goal News|language=Greek|access-date=27 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120531001529/http://www.sentragoal.gr/article.asp?catid=10532&subid=2&pubid=129050666|archive-date=31 May 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"sp24\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Olympiakos/sthn_athhna_o_ntielna.1788400.html|title=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1 \u03bf \u039d\u03c4\u03b9\u03b5\u03bb\u03bd\u03ac (Dielna in Athens)|date=24 May 2012|publisher=Sport24|language=Greek}}</ref> He also helped the side win the French national titles during his time there.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: New-boy Dielna issues promise to Owls fans|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-new-boy-dielna-issues-promise-to-owls-fans-1-6815123|publisher=The Star|date=31 August 2014|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Olympiacos===\nHe signed for [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] in late May 2012 as a [[free agent]] on a three-year contract.<ref name=\"goal\"/><ref name=\"sp24\"/> However, Manager [[Leonardo Jardim]] placed Dielna on a loan list.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u039a\u03af\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u039d\u03c4\u03b9\u03b5\u03bb\u03bd\u03ac \u03bf \u039b\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b4\u03b5\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Levadiakos/kinhsh-gia-ntielna-o-levadeiakos.1883836.html|publisher=Sport24|language=Greek|date=7 August 2012|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nImmediately after joining Olympiacos, Dielna returned to France, where he joined [[CS Sedan Ardennes|Sedan]] on a season long loan.<ref>{{cite news|title=Foot - Transferts : Dielna arrive \u00e0 Sedan|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Dielna-arrive-a-sedan/308840|publisher=L'Equipe|language=French|date=27 August 2012|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> Dielna made his debut for the club, days later after joining the club, in a 2-2 draw against Caen. Dielna would go on to make twenty-five appearance and score two goals against [[Tours FC|Tours]]<ref>{{cite news|title=: Caen, \u00e7a repart|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Caen-ca-repart/352342|publisher=L'Equipe|language=French|date=22 February 2013|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> and [[AC Arles-Avignon|Arles-Avignon]]<ref>{{cite news|title=(J29) : LENS S\u2019IMPOSE FACE \u00c0 AUXERRE|url=http://www.football365.fr/j29-lens-simpose-face-a-auxerre-1924949.html|publisher=Football 365|language=French|date=15 March 2013|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> for the club.\n\nAt the start of the 2013-14 season, Dielna loaned out again to join Ligue 1 side [[AC Ajaccio|Ajaccio]] on a season long loan.<ref>{{cite news|title=Transferts - Dielna \u00e0 Ajaccio|url=http://www.goal.com/fr/news/33/transferts/2013/06/29/4083073/transferts-dielna-%C3%A0-ajaccio|publisher=Goal.com|language=French|date=29 June 2013|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> Dielna went on to make twenty-two appearance for the club, though his spell was overshadowed by claims he fell out with manager [[Fabrizio Ravanelli]].<ref name=\"GetFrenchFootballNews\">{{cite news|title=In Depth Interview: Claude Dielna|url=http://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2014/in-depth-interview-claude-dielna/|publisher=Get French Football News|date=10 September 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> However, at the end of the season, Ajaccio were relegated to Ligue 2 and Dielna announced that he will be returning to Olympiacos.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u039d\u03c4\u03b9\u03b5\u03bb\u03bd\u03ac: \"\u0395\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03c1\u03ad\u03c6\u03c9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c3\u03b5\u03b6\u03cc\u03bd\"|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/France/ntielna-epistrefw-sthn-ellada-sto-telos-ths-sezon.2429949.html|publisher=Sport24|language=Greek|date=27 September 2013|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> Dielna cited the club's relegation was over injury problems.<ref name=\"GetFrenchFootballNews\"/>\n\n===Sheffield Wednesday===\nOn 30 August 2014, Dielna signed a three-year deal with English championship side [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swfc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-wednesday-sign-european-defender-1885660.aspx |title=Sheffield Wednesday sign European defender |publisher=Sheffield Wednesday F.C. |accessdate=30 December 2014 |date=30 August 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141230142207/http://www.swfc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-wednesday-sign-european-defender-1885660.aspx |archivedate=30 December 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Dielna's move to the club was welcomed by [[R\u00e9da Johnson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swfc.co.uk/news/article/big-move-for-claude-dielna-says-reda-johnson-1893250.aspx |title=Big move for Claude Dielna says Reda Johnson |publisher=Sheffield Wednesday F.C. |accessdate=30 December 2014 |date=2 September 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141230142200/http://www.swfc.co.uk/news/article/big-move-for-claude-dielna-says-reda-johnson-1893250.aspx |archivedate=30 December 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nDielna made his debut for the club, where he came on as a substitute for [[Jacques Maghoma]] in the last minute, in a 1-0 win over [[Reading F.C.|Reading]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday 1-0 Reading|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29186723|publisher=BBC Sport|date=20 September 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> Then, on 6 December 2014, Dielna scored his first goal for the club after coming on as an 88th-minute substitute and scoring the winner in 93rd minute to win 2-1 over [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackburn Rovers 1-2 Sheffield Wednesday|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30256840|publisher=BBC Sport|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> His good display in the match earned him included Football League Team of the Week for the Championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swfc.co.uk/news/article/dielna-makes-team-of-the-week-2131863.aspx |title=Dielna makes Team of the Week |publisher=Sheffield Wednesday F.C. |accessdate=30 December 2014 |date=8 December 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141230143604/http://www.swfc.co.uk/news/article/dielna-makes-team-of-the-week-2131863.aspx |archivedate=30 December 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Initially out of the first team since joining the club, due to his match fitness and sharpness, Dielna soon established himself in the first team despite facing competitions from [[Joe Mattock]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018Dedicated\u2019 Claude Dielna aims to cement starting berth|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-dedicated-claude-dielna-aims-to-cement-starting-berth-1-6931726|publisher=The Star|date=7 November 2014|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> His performance attracted interests from [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Brom]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday defender came close to Serie A move|url=https://talksport.com/football/sheffield-wednesday-defender-came-close-serie-move-15021113600|publisher=TalkSport|date=8 January 2015|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> and [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday defender came close to Serie A move|url=https://talksport.com/football/sheffield-wednesday-defender-came-close-serie-move-150211136003|publisher=TalkSport|date=11 February 2015|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> Despite this, he continued that run until an injury struck out for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: Depleted Owls eye back-to-basics approach|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-depleted-owls-eye-back-to-basics-approach-1-7203527|publisher=The Star|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2015/april/owls-suffer-dielna-blow/|title=Owls suffer Dielna blow|publisher=Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|date=6 April 2015|accessdate=11 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811195329/https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2015/april/owls-suffer-dielna-blow/|archivedate=11 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In his first season at Sheffield Wednesday, Dielna made twenty-five appearances and scoring three times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2015-16 season, Dielna, however, found himself out of the first team, due to his own injury concern and was dropped out by new Manager [[Carlos Carvalhal]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: Relaxed Carlos ready for Robins test|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-relaxed-carlos-ready-for-robins-test-1-7397652|publisher=The Star|date=7 August 2015|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: A player has asked to leave reveals Carvalhal|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-a-player-has-asked-to-leave-reveals-carvalhal-1-7433062|publisher=The Star|date=27 August 2015|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> With his future at the club uncertain, Dielna was told by the club that he can leave the club on loan.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: Fringe men can leave on loan, admits Owls boss|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-fringe-men-can-leave-on-loan-admits-owls-boss-1-7685957|publisher=The Star|date=21 January 2016|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> He was subsequently loaned out to [[\u0160K Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]] for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2016/february/dielna-completes-loan-move-to-sk-slovan-bratislava/|title=Dielna completes loan move to SK Slovan Bratislava|publisher=Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|date=26 February 2016|accessdate=11 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811201550/https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2016/february/dielna-completes-loan-move-to-sk-slovan-bratislava/|archivedate=11 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his Slovan Bratislava debut, where he came on as a second-half substitute, in a 1-0 win over [[FK \u017deleziarne Podbrezov\u00e1|\u017deleziarne Podbrezov\u00e1]] on 5 March 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fortuna liga: Slovan ani Tren\u010d\u00edn na ihrisk\u00e1ch s\u00faperov nezav\u00e1hali|url=https://sport.sme.sk/c/8149201/fortuna-liga-slovan-ani-trencin-na-ihriskach-superov-nezavahali.html|publisher=Sport.sme.sk|language=Slovak|date=5 March 2016|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> Dielna went on to make six appearances for the club before returning to his parent club at the end of the season.\n\nIn the 2016-17 season, Dielna was placed on a transfer list by Manager Carvalhal upon returning to his parent club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: Owls make trio available|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-owls-make-trio-available-1-8017134|publisher=The Star|date=16 July 2016|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> Amid to being placed on the transfer list, Dielna was disciplined by the club for breaching the club's policy on social media and was subsequently suspended.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: Claude Dielna in hot water after social media outburst|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-claude-dielna-in-hot-water-after-social-media-outburst-1-8101444|publisher=The Star|date=1 September 2016|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> He remained out of the first team throughout the most of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: Owls willing to let fringe players leave in January|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-owls-willing-to-let-fringe-players-leave-in-january-1-8305259|publisher=The Star|date=23 December 2016|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> After being told by the club that he can leave the club,<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield Wednesday: Quartet free to go as Carlos Carvalhal looks to reshape Owls squad|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-wednesday/sheffield-wednesday-quartet-free-to-go-as-carlos-carvalhal-looks-to-reshape-owls-squad-1-8329180|publisher=The Star|date=12 January 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> Dielna joined Romanian side [[FC Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti|Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti]] on loan for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2017/february/dielna-joins-dinamo-bucharest/|title=Dielna joins Dinamo Bucharest|publisher=Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|date=6 February 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811204413/https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2017/february/dielna-joins-dinamo-bucharest/|archivedate=11 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut for club, starting the whole game, in a 2-1 loss against [[CS Concordia Chiajna|Concordia Chiajna]] on 13 February 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=VIDEO Dinam-out? Trupa lui Andone a pierdut al treilea meci consecutiv \u015fi tremur\u0103 serios pentru un loc \u00een play-off: 1-2 cu Chiajna|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/video-dinam-out-trupa-lui-andone-a-pierdut-al-treilea-meci-consecutiv-si-tremura-serios-pentru-un-loc-in-play-off-1-2-cu-chiajna-501943.html|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=14 February 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> Although he suffered a muscle injury later in the season,<ref>{{cite news|title=St\u0103 3 s\u0103pt\u0103m\u00e2ni! S-a accidentat cu Craiova \u015fi va rata returul Cupei Ligii cu Steaua|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/sta-3-saptamani-s-a-accidentat-cu-craiova-si-va-rata-returul-cupei-ligii-cu-steaua-503120.html|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=27 February 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> Dielna managed to regained his first team since his return and made seventeen appearances for the side.<ref>{{cite news|title=Se bat cu Sunderland \u00bb Dinamovi\u015ftii i-au oferit lui Dielna un salariu-record pentru actualul lot al \"c\u00e2inilor\"|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/se-bat-cu-sunderland-dinamovistii-i-au-oferit-lui-dielna-un-salariu-record-pentru-actualul-lot-al-cainilor-511043.html|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=18 May 2016|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Se destram\u0103 Dinamo la finalul sezonului? 9 juc\u0103tori \u0219i antrenorul sunt pe picior de plecare|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/se-destrama-dinamo-la-finalul-sezonului-9-jucatori-si-antrenorul-sunt-pe-picior-de-plecare-510292.html|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=10 May 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n   \nUpon returning to his parent club, Dielna was released by the club at the end of the 2016-17 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2017/may/owls-confirm-out-of-contract-players/|title=Owls confirm out of contract players|publisher=Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|date=20 May 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811210031/https://www.swfc.co.uk/news/2017/may/owls-confirm-out-of-contract-players/|archivedate=11 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===New England Revolution===\nAfter being released by Sheffield Wednesday, Dielna was linked a move to Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti.<ref>{{cite news|title=EXCLUSIV Juc\u0103torul pentru care insist\u0103 Dinamo vrea s\u0103 fie cel mai bine pl\u0103tit din Liga 1 \u00bb Cere un salariu enorm|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/exclusiv-jucatorul-pentru-care-insista-dinamo-vrea-sa-fie-cel-mai-bine-platit-din-liga-1-cere-un-salariu-enorm-513416.html|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=13 June 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> Instead, Dielna signed with [[Major League Soccer]] side [[New England Revolution]] on 28 July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.revolutionsoccer.net/post/2017/07/28/revolution-sign-defender-claude-dielna|title=New England Revolution Sign Defender Claude Dielna|publisher=New England Revolution|date=28 July 2017|accessdate=11 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811210519/https://www.revolutionsoccer.net/post/2017/07/28/revolution-sign-defender-claude-dielna|archivedate=11 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nNew England released Dielna at the end of their 2018 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2018/11/05/new-england-revolution-announce-end-season-roster-moves |title=New England Revolution announce end of season roster moves |publisher=MLSsoccer.com |date=2019-04-02 |accessdate=2019-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|21 July 2018|<ref>{{LFP|id=dielna-claude}}</ref><ref>{{MLS|claude-dielna}}</ref><ref>{{Soccerway|claude-dielna/44832}}</ref>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|Domestic Cup<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Includes the [[Coupe de France]], [[FA Cup]], and [[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]]</ref>\n!colspan=2|League Cup<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Includes the [[Coupe de la Ligue]], [[Football League Cup|League Cup]], and [[Cupa Ligii]]</ref>\n!colspan=2|Continental\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[FC Lorient|Lorient]]\n|[[2006\u201307 Ligue 1|2006\u201307]]\n|[[Ligue 1]]\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||colspan=2|\u2013||0||0\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 Ligue 1|2007\u201308]]\n|Ligue 1\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||colspan=2|\u2013||0||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|To